TITLE:: Synesthesia
summary:: A live-coding vocabulary where the patch is the canvas and patterns are brushes
categories:: Live Coding
related:: Overviews/JITLib

DESCRIPTION::
Synesthesia is a personal live-coding language layered over JITLib/ProxySpace.
Its registers: painting words for timbre and texture (colors as HSV timbre
coordinates, tools as applicators), music words for pitch and time, systems words
for topology — all evaluating to plain SuperCollider objects so raw SC composes
anywhere.

This is the Phase 0 skeleton. The vocabulary arrives in Phases 1–2; see the
Roadmap in the author's Live-Coding-With-SuperCollider repository.

CLASSMETHODS::

METHOD:: version
The quark version string.

METHOD:: dir
The quark's root folder on disk.
